modules.description: This module handles the rewriting of i18n-related expressions during OCaml compilation. It transforms translation placeholders into references to generated translation modules, using configurable module naming conventions. Key operations include constructing identifiers, applying translation functions, and expanding expressions with localization context. It is used to implement compile-time internationalization support in OCaml projects.

This module processes i18n placeholders in OCaml source code during compilation, transforming them into references to translation modules. It constructs identifiers, applies translation functions, and expands expressions with localization context, based on configurable module naming. It enables compile-time internationalization by integrating translation keys and metadata directly into the compiled code structure.
